\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Click the Bracket Tool (shown above).   Next click-and-hold-down on a staff, and drag to another staff on the system.   Dragging the cursor up or down will move the initial endpoint (down) or extend the bracket (up).  Releasing will connect the selected range of staves with a system bracket.  This tool is one-shot, so the palette will revert to the Selection tool when the bracket is constructed.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b To alter the bracket placement\b0  \par
